= Questions of Ideology

The <span style="color: var(--nlp-color);">**[+ nlp_name +]**</span> is torn between many different ideological currents. What should be our primary ideological guidance for now?

[? if ideology != 0 : We have previously chosen a [+ ideology +] ideology. Changing it will likely have drawbacks. ?]

- @left_stresemannite: The party should emphasize Stresemann’s spirit of pragmatic cooperation between the Weimar Parties and us.
- @right_stresemannite: The party should emphasize Stresemann’s nationalistic zeal whilst maintaining the status of Republican by Reason.
- @labor: We must pursue the idea of the Volksgemeinschaft, poaching nationalistic elements of the worker’s movement.
- @industrialist: Our contacts with big business should be deepened, the industrial magnates need a party to represent them.
- @easy_discard

@left_stresemannite
on-arrival: {!
if (Q.ideology && Q.ideology != "Left-wing Stresemannite") {
    Q.changed = 1;
}
!}
go-to: changed if changed = 1
on-departure: ideology = "Left-wing Stresemannite"; left_stresemannite_strength += 10; left_stresemannite_dissent -= 5; spd_relation += 3; dnvp_relation -= 5;

Our party has largely survived thanks to the efforts of our party leader, Gustav Stresemann. A key element in his leadership has been a spirit of pragmatism towards the traditionally republican parties of the <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span>, <span style="color: #000000;">**Z**</span>, and the <span style="color: #FFD800;">**FVP**</span>; we should continue to work with the Weimar Parties if it furthers our interests.

@right_stresemannite
