on-departure: ideology = "labor"; labor_strength += 10; labor_dissent -= 5;

The simmering discontent brought by the German Empire’s defeat in WW1 [? if uspd_exist: and the splintering of the <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span>’s dominance ?] has opened a path for more right-leaning movements to gain traction amongst the working classes. Some of our own party members — particularly those who are also part of the DHV (German National Association of Commercial Employees), and led by a relative newcomer in Otto Thiel — have begun calling for a greater focus on the worker in our party manifesto.

